Subject: [PATCH 352/452] staging: fsl-mc: set IORESOURCE_CACHEABLE

Adding code to copy the cacheability attribute from flags in
struct dprc_region_desc to flags in struct resource. This enables
MC device drivers to check the cacheability of regions in MC devices.

Signed-off-by: Itai Katz <itai.katz@freescale.com>
[Xulin: Original patch taken from FSL LS2085 SDK EAR6.0,
LS2085A-SDK-SOURCE-20160304-yocto.iso]
Signed-off-by: Xulin Sun <xulin.sun@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/staging/fsl-mc/bus/mc-bus.c |    2 ++
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/staging/fsl-mc/bus/mc-bus.c b/drivers/staging/fsl-mc/bus/mc-bus.c
index b12cd9b..2e11474 100644
--- a/drivers/staging/fsl-mc/bus/mc-bus.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/fsl-mc/bus/mc-bus.c
@@ -493,6 +493,8 @@ static int fsl_mc_device_get_mmio_regions(struct fsl_mc_device *mc_dev,
 		regions[i].end = regions[i].start + region_desc.size - 1;
 		regions[i].name = "fsl-mc object MMIO region";
 		regions[i].flags = IORESOURCE_IO;
+		if (region_desc.flags & DPRC_REGION_CACHEABLE)
+			regions[i].flags |= IORESOURCE_CACHEABLE;
 	}
 
 	mc_dev->regions = regions;
